        ],
        [
          "Clustering",
          "Higher Education",
          "E-Learning",
          "366 undergraduate students",
          "Diverse Majors in Science, Humanities and Social Sciences",
          "Internet Self-Efficacy Survey,\nOAHS questionnaire",
          "Online Help-Seeking and Internet Self-Efficacy",
          "[Infoormation Searching, Formal query, Informal query, Usage, Sharing, Communication, Verifying, Metacognition, Application, Learning]",
          "OAHS questionnaire is a 5-point Likert Scale, ISE is also a 5-point Likert Scale",
          "k-Means",
          "ANOVA and Scheffé Tests",
          "3",
          "Cluster 1 - Adaptive: More diverse experiences across OAHS experiences and higher confidence across ISE scales. 169 participants\n\nCluster 2 - Socially Afilliated: Higher scores on Formal and Informal Query than  Query than self-reliant. On ISE - more sharing. 134 participants\n\nCluster 3 - Self-Reliant: Better at Information Searching. Also, theses students have also shown higher confidence in ISE Usage.\n\n",
          "- System developers could set-up multiple help-seeking channels since different students have different habits\n\n- Develop adaptive help-seeking detection and regulation mechanisms in computer environments.\n\n- Organaize tasks and pedagogies across new learning paradigms (e.g. PBL) to form a trusted online learning community - something the authors argue is bvaluable.",
          "Authors do 2 surveys to 366 undergrads across different taiwanese institutions.\n\nFrom the surveys the authors cluster the students into 3 distinct clusters using k-means.\n\nResults show that there seem to be 3 main kinds of online help-seeking behavior and each has different preferences and psychological attributes.",
          "- Only  considers Taiwanese Context\n\n- Only uses surveys as source of information\n\n- Only considers 3 OAHS patterns.Including more could probably lead to the creation of other categories\n\n- There does not seem to be made a normalization for different fields - groups may be overly general."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
  ],
